name: nitrate reductase (quinone)
classes: Acting on other nitrogenous compounds as donors;
With a quinone or similar compound as acceptor
reaction: nitrate + a quinol = nitrite + a quinone + H2O [RN:R09497]
comment: A membrane-bound enzyme which supports anaerobic respiration on nitrate under anaerobic conditions and in the presence of nitrate. Contains the bicyclic form of the molybdo-bis(molybdopterin guanine dinucleotide) cofactor, iron-sulfur clusters and heme b. Escherichia coli expresses two forms NarA and NarZ, both being comprised of three subunits.

orthologs.K00370: nitrate reductase / nitrite oxidoreductase, alpha subunit
orthologs.K00371: nitrate reductase / nitrite oxidoreductase, beta subunit
